SIMPLE: negligent
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Negligent
<hw>Neg"li*gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧gligent</ets>, L. <ets>negligens</ets>,p. pr. of
<ets>negligere</ets>. See <er>Neglect</er>.]</ety> <def>Apt to neglect;
customarily neglectful; characterized by negligence; careless; heedless;
culpably careless; showing lack of attention; <as>as, disposed in
<ex>negligent</ex> order</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Be thou <xex>negligent</xex>
of fame.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that thinks he can afford to be <qex>negligent</qex> is not far
from being poor.</q> <rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Careles; heedless; neglectful; regardless;
thoughtless; indifferent; inattentive; remiss.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Negligently</ent>⟦br⟧
